	   <tr><td colspan=2>I do believe I did a post earlier about this.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'll just bring it back. *grin*<br><br>Combat-oriented paladins: Dwarves. No question. They may not cast as well as other races, but they have the highest combat statistics. However, I can't stand their diety, and they're short. :P Dwarven Paladins must worship Brell Serilis.   (Actually, Dwarves have the highest paladin statistics period.  Found that out later.)<br><br>Well-rounded paladins: Humans or Half-Elves. The primary advantage of being a half-elf is the vision. Infravision is better than being blind, but they do have lower wisdom, so you'll have to pump that up a bit to make up for it. However, I'm human myself, and I've never had any problems fitting any role a group would want me in. Humans may follow Erollisi or Mithaniel Marr, Karana, or Rodcet Nife. Half-Elves can also follow Tunare. <br><br>Caster paladins: High Elves. They have the highest wisdom of all the races, but low strength. They also have vision. High Elves must worship Tunare. <br><br>Very rare paladins: Erudites. They.. uh.. Are kina.. *shrug* Low statistics. Erudites can follow Prexus and Quellious.<br><br>I myself am a human paladin of Erollisi Marr.  A good friend of mine (who I WILL beat one day in a drinking contest) is half-elf of Mithaniel and likes it.<br>&nbsp;<br>Dalantia Dragonfury<br>Crusader of the Burning Heart, 60th Protection, Third Blessing<br>Fennin Ro<br>New Dawnings<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60479" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60479</a></td></tr>
