	   <tr><td colspan=2>Jagged Bands and Orc fang earrings are really nice pieces, and the Bronze BP can last you till you get a BP of Ro or better. Someone here (Praetor I think) had a guide of where to get bronze armor... look at that, and try to upgrade your banded to bronze. (You might have to wait a few levels). Bronze is in no way bad armor (I dont know why people think that it is), and can last you for many levels.<br><br>Just keep upgrading, and you will see that you will have some pretty nice armor after a while. I just keep getting armor (Like Val now from fear raids) which lets me either sell the stuff for cash, or give it to my guild members.<br><br>If you are in a guild, most of the time the members wont want to waste a whole lot of time in EC, so they will either give you the item, or sell it to your for very cheap. This is a good thing to watch out for.<br><br>As for going to IWK, I would definately wait a few levels, as just getting there would be a big problem, and you would be killed in one round. If you can get there though, the shield drops off of all the guards I think, so most groups will just give them away to you if you need it.<br>&nbsp;<br>Caledonia Delacroix<br>47th Level Paladin<br>Proud Member of <b>The White Cross</b><br>E`ci Server</td></tr>
