	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.51]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, cant say for sure if you got the better end of the deal money wise (Items run for different prices on every server) but I know that in the end run, if you are not fighting undead, the M2H is the best way to go. I remember when this used to be THE weapon. It is a very fine weapon and will last you for a long time.<br><br>I personally like to keep both a 1hs and a 2hs on me, and I use my GB still when fighting undead (You will be amazed how much it procs when you have a decent dex buff).<br><br>At level 20, you just have had the damage cap taken off, but since you are not that high in the weapon skill, only expect to hit for about 45 max (Mebbe a little more or less depending on STR). As you level, and you weapon skill goes up, so will the amount of damage that you do.<br><br>One of the reasons that the M2H makes such a good sword is, with a base DLY of 40, it gets the damage bonus for 2h weapons with delay of 40+, plus you get the haste on it, which makes you attack faster, making you do even more damage.<br><br>As for getting your skill up, just keep fighting, and your skill will go up. However, try to keep all of your skills up, cause starting from 0 at a high level can be a real pain.<br><br>Hope this helps.<br>&nbsp;<br>Caledonia Delacroix<br>47th Level Paladin<br>Proud Member of <b>The White Cross</b><br>E`ci Server</td></tr>
